using namespace std;

int a[6][6];

int check(int x, int y)
{
    int count = 0;
    for( int i=x-1; i<x+2; i++)
         for( int j=y-1; j<y+2; j++)
         {
              if( i==x && j==y )
                  continue;
              if( a[i][j]==1 )
                  count++;
         }
    if( a[x-1][y-1]==a[x][y-1] && a[x-1][y-1]==a[x-1][y] && a[x-1][y-1]==1 )
        count = 6;
    else if( a[x-1][y]==a[x-1][y+1] && a[x-1][y]==a[x][y+1] && a[x-1][y]==1 )
             count = 6;
    else if( a[x][y-1]==a[x+1][y-1] && a[x][y-1]==a[x+1][y] && a[x][y-1]==1 )
             count = 6;
    else if( a[x][y+1]==a[x+1][y+1] && a[x][y+1]==a[x+1][y] && a[x][y+1]==1 ) 
             count = 6;
              
    return count;                       
}

int main()
{
    int t, p, i, j;
    cin>>t;
    for( p=0; p<t; p++)
    {
         int flag = 0;
         for( i=0; i<6; i++)
              for( j=0; j<6; j++)
                   cin>>a[i][j];
         for( i=1; i<5; i++)
              for( j=1; j<5; j++)
                   if( a[i][j]==1 )
                   {
                       int res = check(i,j);
                       if( res > 4)
                       {
                           flag = 1;
                           break;
                       }
                       else if( res==4 )
                       {
                            if( a[i-2][j]!=1 && a[i][j-2]!=1 && a[i][j+2]!=1 && a[i+2][j]!=1 )
                            {
                                flag = 1;
                                break;            
                            }                
                       }         
                   }
                                     
         
         if( flag==0)
             cout<<"correct"<<endl;
         else 
             cout<<"incorrect"<<endl;     
                            
    }
    //getch();
    return 0;    
}
